<br>
I wish I understood what exactly VI's plan for our class is.  Where do we fit in &quot;The Vision(TM)?&quot;  And why is it that whenever somebody suggests giving something to mages that perhaps slightly infringes on another class, it's unacceptable because it blurs the distinction between classes...  but yet other classes constantly get new tricks that are not only within our sphere of expertise, but <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> better</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> than what we do.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong here, please!  I'm not denying those other classes their right to new and cool stuff.  Far from it, I think that it's pretty cool that Druids are getting such a useful spell.  The Enchanter nuke, nice...  Good for them!  But what about us?  Why do we get a nuke that is only marginally better than what we've already got?  Why give us another pet buff when half the time we're forbidden from using pets anyway (heh, unless a Level 60 player is planning on doing a lot of soloing.  Gotta get them AA points I guess)<br>
<br>
I don't want them to stop improving other classes...  I just want them to improve us for once.  I guess in a way this <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a case of class envy...  I envy the other classes for getting attention when I feel that we deserve some too. <p><BR><CENTER><hr size=1 WIDTH=75%>
