class envy? ha.<br>
<br>
if wanting to be equally as useful as other classes means that im jealous, than so be it. im jealous. <br>
<br>
but keep in mind, youre <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   also</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> jealous if you think the mage class is weak. consider the following: <br>
<br>
1) a class being &quot;weak&quot;, &quot;underpowered&quot;, ect in essence means <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that they have less potent net ability than that of other classes. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   they are weak in comparison to other classes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
2) your relative strength comparied to the other classes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   is the only unit of measure for class power</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
3) a player of a class who views themselves as &quot;weak&quot;, of course means they feel their abilities should be as good, or better than the abilities some other classes have. therefore, they desire increases to their current skills till they are similar or greater than other classes.<br>
4) you have wrongly defined this third point as &quot;class envy&quot;.<br>
if you have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   ever</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> called a class weak, you are then a hypocrite. by calling the mage class weak, you are wishing they were as strong as other classes, which would be being <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  envious</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of them...<br>
<br>
<br>
